Mar 16 2007 	Stay Elsewhere	I stayed here for 3 nights on a business trip. Outside of a meager buffet breakfast, the food I had in the dining room was overpriced and poor. The &quot;renovation&quot; other reviewers have talked about for months has made little progress. The printer for the public computer was out of order. The room was so close to I-90 and the train that it was very hard to sleep at all. To top it off, in the middle of one night the hotel staff were trying to break down the door of the next room for a guest because their key did not let them back in. The clerk at the desk just laughed when contacted.	
